#~ msgid ""
#~ "Generates an intensity profile plot between 2 points in each image in the "
#~ "sequence. The arguments may be provided in any order. The arguments <b>-"
#~ "to=x,y</b> and <b>-from=x,y</b> are mandatory.\n"
#~ "\n"
#~ "The argument <b>-layer=<i>{red | green | blue | lum | col}</i></b> "
#~ "specifies which channel (or luminance or colour) to plot if the image is "
#~ "color. This can be used in conjunction with spectrometric options. It may "
#~ "also be used with the <b>-tri</b> option, which generates 3 parallel "
#~ "equispaced profiles each separated by <b>-spacing=</b> pixels, but note "
#~ "that for tri profiles the <i><b>col</b></i> option will be treated the "
#~ "same as <i><b>lum</b></i>.\n"
#~ "\n"
#~ "The option <b>-cfa</b> selects CFA mode, which generates 4 profiles: 1 "
#~ "for each CFA channel in a Bayer patterned image. This option cannot be "
#~ "used with color images or mono images with no Bayer pattern, and cannot "
#~ "be used at the same time as the <b>-tri</b> option.\n"
#~ "\n"
#~ "The option <b>-arcsec</b> causes the x axis to display distance in "
#~ "arcsec, if the necessary metadata is available. This option is overridden "
#~ "if spectrometric options are provided. If not provided or if metadata is "
#~ "not available, distance will be shown in pixel units.\n"
#~ "\n"
#~ "The <b>-savedat</b> argument may be provided if it is desired to keep the "
#~ "GNUplot data files: by default they will be deleted.\n"
#~ "\n"
#~ "<b>Spectrometric Options</b>\n"
#~ "\n"
#~ "If spectrometric options are provided, all of the following must be "
#~ "provided: <b>-wavenumber1=</b> and <b>-wavenumber2=</b> specify 2 "
#~ "wavenumbers in cm<sup>-1</sup>, and <b>-wn1=x,y</b> and <b>-wn2=x,y</b> "
#~ "specify points in the image corresponding to those wavenumbers. As a "
#~ "convenience, <b>-wavelength1=</b> and <b>-wavelength2=</b> may be used "
#~ "instead to provide wavelengths in nm. These are always converted and the "
#~ "plot axis always shows wavenumber. The optional spectrometric argument "
#~ "<b>-width=</b> may be provided, which specifies how many pixels should be "
#~ "averaged perpendicular to the profile line.\n"
#~ "\n"
#~ "The argument <b>\"-title=<i>My Title\"</i></b> sets a custom title \"My "
#~ "Title\". If processing a sequence and it is desired to have the current "
#~ "image number and total number of images displayed in the format \"My "
